article.headline: CS Northridge 91, UC Irvine 83
article.story: NORTHRIDGE, Calif. -- Lenny Daniel snagged a double-double, scoring 22 points and pulling down 10 rebounds, to lead Cal State Northridge over UC Irvine 91-83 on Saturday night. It was Daniel's 10th double-double in the past 14 games for the Matadors (9-14, 6-4 Big West). Northridge shot 54.2 percent from the field and won the fourth of its last five games. Rashaun McLemore added 18 points for the Matadors while Josh Greene scored 13 and Aqeel Quinn 12. Darren Moore led the Anteaters (10-14, 3-7) with 20 points, including shooting 11 of 14 from the free throw line. Patrick Rembert added 14 points and Daman Starring 12 for Irvine. The Anteaters shot just 37.9 percent from the field.
